The paper discusses the efficient tuning of hyperparameters for deep reinforcement learning agents and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of iterative processes, which suggests a possible fit with the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
